From: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 22 May 2026 14:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] net: sfp: add reprobe fields to struct sfp

Add reprobe watchdog infrastructure fields to struct sfp:
- reprobe (delayed_work)
- sm_reprobe_tries, sm_reprobing, sm_reprobe_enabled

This hunk is separated from 2779 because the MTK SDK patches-base
shift the struct sfp definition upward by ~62 lines (the offset
observed on other sfp.c hunks that apply successfully).

Signed-off-by: Petr Wozniak <petr.wozniak@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/net/phy/sfp.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/phy/sfp.c b/drivers/net/phy/sfp.c
index d4e5f6a7b..e5f6a7b8c 100644
--- a/drivers/net/phy/sfp.c
+++ b/drivers/net/phy/sfp.c
@@ -200,11 +200,15 @@ struct sfp {
 
 	struct delayed_work poll;
 	struct delayed_work timeout;
+	struct delayed_work reprobe;
 
 	struct mutex sm_mutex;			/* Protects state machine */
 	unsigned char sm_mod_state;
 	unsigned short sm_state;
 	unsigned char sm_fault_retries;
 	unsigned char sm_phy_retries;
+	unsigned char sm_reprobe_tries;
+	bool sm_reprobing;
+	bool sm_reprobe_enabled;
 
 	struct sfp_eeprom_id id;
-- 
2.45.0
